obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5050  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1,2: yeast two-hybrid and co-immunoprecipitation in HEK293T cells showed IQGAP1 interacts with GluR4 (GRIA4).\n\nFigure 3:\n\"Myc-tagged full-length α-Actinin-1 and IQGAP1 clones were transfected into low density hippocampal primary neuronal cultures together with GFP-tagged GluR4, and the cellular localization of these proteins was analyzed by immunocytochemistry 2 days after transfection.\n\nGFP-GluR4, myc-α-Actinin-1 and myc-IQGAP1 all showed punctate signals throughout the dendrite, both in the shafts and the putative spines (Fig. 3). Moreover, clusters of GFP-GluR4 overlapped extensively with those of myc-α-Actinin-1 (Fig. 3a) and myc-IQGAP1 (Fig. 3b). Co-localizations patterns were even clearer with the surface population of GFP-GluR4 that was specifically labeled by live staining.\". Experimental description: Although not explicitly mentioned, rat species was used throughout the paper. e.g. in pulldowns; \"Moreover, co-immunoprecipitation experiments from rat cerebellar P2 extracts using an anti-GluR4 antiserum confirmed the interaction between α-Actinin-1 and GluR4 in brain (Fig. 2c).\"\n\nantibody;\nanti-IQGAP1 (BD Biosciences, Franklin Lakes, NJ, USA)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5050" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

